==Swedish==
'''Norden''', the [[nordic]] countries.
# Name of the country group of [[Denmark]], [[Iceland]], [[Norway]], [[Finland]] and [[Sweden]]. ''[[Scandinavia]]'' comprises the subgroup Denmark, Norway and Sweden.

N B:
*''[[The Faroes]]'' is part of Denmark, but self ruling since 1948. Denmark is member of the [[European Union]], but the Faroes not. Nevertheless the Faroes is generally considered to belong to ''Norden''. 
*''[[Greenland]]'' is also part of Denmark, but self ruling since 1979. In spite of the fact that Greenland geographically is not [[Europe]] but [[North America]], it initially was a member of the European Union. Greenland, however, discontinued membership in the European Union 1982. Greenland generally is considered not to belong to ''Norden''.

